[thinking] 
[thinking] Inner entity classes can definitely be public static, as JPA works well with them. If the top-level class is public, that’s fine too! It uses reflection, which is helpful. I want to avoid unnecessary characters like `$` in the file or test names—StatefulPersistenceContextTest works well. Regarding naming, it’s okay for inner classes to have `$`, but not for the test class. I should also consider line length for Checkstyle and maybe keep some classes package-private instead of public. Lastly, I will stick with AssertJ for assertions.
